<title type="html"><![CDATA[1/25--11 Crazy Ways The Weather Influences Your Health and Behavior/ Understanding Foreign Cultures By Eating Their Food]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=117&amp;p=121#p121"><![CDATA[
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: #0040FF">Host: Johnny</span></span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session I</span><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">11 Crazy Ways The Weather Influences Your Health and Behavior</span><br /><a href="https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/weather-and-health_us_570facd9e4b08a2d32b92ae9" class="postlink">https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/weather-and-health_us_570facd9e4b08a2d32b92ae9</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion:</span><br />1.Please name one or two points of view in this article that you could not agree with more and explain why.<br />2.Do you or your family members have any health problems when weather changes? (Such us sneezing, stuffy nose, chapped lips, achy joints, headache, high/low blood pressure and so on.)<br />3.Are you a hot weather person or a cold weather lover? Why? (What are your favorite and least favorite seasons of the year? What makes it unique or different from other seasons to you?)<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session II</span><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Understanding Foreign Cultures By Eating Their Food</span><br /><a href="http://www.newsweek.com/understanding-foreign-cultures-eating-their-food-92593" class="postlink">http://www.newsweek.com/understanding-foreign-cultures-eating-their-food-92593</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion:</span><br />1.What is the food style that you most prefer, Chinese, Japanese, Thai, or western style?<br />2.Do you trust in Michelin Stars? Have you ever try the restaurant that Michelin guide to recommend to you? Please share your opinion or experience.<br />3.Food culture depends on what is the crops we plant, so do you believe in it shape us to be different with western people even the Africa people?<br />4.In many cases, foreign cuisine would change the flavor to makes acceptable to local. How about you? Do you like to taste the original or the changed flavor?<br />5.Do you think the night market foods can represent Taiwan's food feature? Please share your thought with everyone.<br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00-7:25 Greetings and free talk<br />7:25-7:30 Opening remarks/ Newcomers self-introduction/ Grouping<br />(Session I)<br />7:30 ~ 8:05pm discussion session (35 mins)<br />8:05 ~ 8:20pm summarization (15 mins)<br />8:20 ~ 8:25pm Regrouping<br />(Session II)<br />8:25 ~ 8:35pm Taking a 10 minutes break (Intermission)<br />8:35 ~ 9:10pm discussion session (35 mins)<br />9:10 ~9:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />9:25 ~ 9:30pm Concluding remarks/feedback from newcomers<br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />摩斯漢堡明曜店 (明曜百貨後面第二條巷子地下室)<br />台北市大安區仁愛路四段151巷37號B1樓<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運 - 板南線 - 忠孝敦化站 (步行約5分鐘)<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500.帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=827">Jason Tang</a> — Sun Jan 21, 2018 7:50 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
